This paper deals with learning disentangled representations for improving fairness in downstream prediction tasks. The paper focuses on high-dimensional observations such as images, which suggests that it could belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. However, the paper also deals with fairness and sensitive variables, which suggests that it could belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the potential for unfairness in predictions, which suggests that it could belong to the cryptography and security (cs.CR) or cybernetics (cs.CY) sub-categories. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG, cs.CV, and cs.AI, followed by cs.CR and cs.CY.
